On Sun, Apr 11, 1999 at 02:52:20PM -0400, David L. Parsley (lkml account) wrote:
> 	Currently, the kernel makes no use of the 'sticky bit' on files
Be careful, there are still installation scripts out there that set the
sticky bit on installed software.  So I consider putting any new
semantics on this bit dangerous.
